      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/4932680/" class="title-link">绝对的好书</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-4932680"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/prodikeys/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1348156-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/prodikeys/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">prodikeys</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2011-05-03"
      class="main-meta">2011-05-03 17:47:19</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_4932680_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  让我一直都在研究思考的问题好像有了答案，这个答案可能就是明与暗的关系。明了就没有暗。这种持续的如实观照不容易，因为我们已经习惯了那种惯性。应反复的练习知道将如实观照成为习惯，也许习惯了那个我就淡了或是消失。还需要再多读几篇可能还有新的感受。继续吧！

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
